# Payment System Architecture — Implementation Plan

## Background & Problem

The existing backend has:
- **[FoodOrderPayment](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Backend/src/modules/food/orders/services/foodOrderPayment.service.js#29-71)** — append-only payment ledger per order event (Razorpay, QR, COD, wallet).
- **`FoodUserWallet`** — user wallet with embedded transactions array (supports top-up via Razorpay, referral rewards).
- **`RestaurantCommissionLedger`** — per-order restaurant commission tracking.
- **Empty stubs** in `core/payments/` (service, controller, routes) and a placeholder BullMQ payment processor.
- **No** delivery partner wallet, settlement/payout model, or refund model.

The goal is to introduce a **full-proof financial layer** with proper separation of concerns, atomic wallet operations, and a settlement/refund system — all adapted to the existing codebase conventions.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Breaking Change: Wallet Migration** — The existing `FoodUserWallet` stores transactions in an embedded array. The new [Wallet](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Backend/src/modules/food/user/services/userWallet.service.js#6-16) model moves to a separate `Transaction` collection. A one-time migration script will be needed to move existing user wallet balances into the new universal [Wallet](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Backend/src/modules/food/user/services/userWallet.service.js#6-16) model. **Existing embedded transactions will be preserved for historical reads** but new transactions will go to the `Transaction` collection.

> [!WARNING]
> **Dual-Write Period** — During the transition, the order service will write to both the existing [FoodOrderPayment](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Backend/src/modules/food/orders/services/foodOrderPayment.service.js#29-71) ledger AND the new `Transaction` collection to avoid breaking existing admin dashboards. Once verified, the old path can be deprecated.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Scope Clarification** — This plan creates the **models + services + routes** on the backend only. Frontend integration (updating [Cart.jsx](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Frontend/src/modules/Food/pages/user/cart/Cart.jsx) to call new payment APIs) is a separate follow-up task. Please confirm if you want frontend changes included in this plan.

