### Phase 2: Core Service Layer

All services go in `Backend/src/core/payments/`.

---

#### [MODIFY] [payment.service.js](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Backend/src/core/payments/payment.service.js)

Currently empty. Will implement:
- `createPayment(orderId, userId, amount, method, gateway)` — creates a Payment record
- `markPaymentSuccess(paymentId, gatewayPaymentId, rawResponse)` — marks paid + triggers ledger entries
- `markPaymentFailed(paymentId, rawResponse)` — marks failed
- `getPaymentsByOrder(orderId)` — list payments for an order

---

#### [NEW] [transaction.service.js](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Backend/src/core/payments/transaction.service.js)

Atomic ledger + wallet operations:
- `recordTransaction(payload)` — creates a Transaction row AND updates corresponding Wallet atomically using MongoDB transactions
- `getTransactionsByEntity(entityType, entityId)` — list ledger entries
- **RULE**: Never update wallet directly — always go through this service

---

#### [NEW] [wallet.service.js](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Backend/src/core/payments/wallet.service.js)

Universal wallet operations:
- `getOrCreateWallet(entityType, entityId)` — ensure wallet exists
- `getBalance(entityType, entityId)` — read balance
- `credit(entityType, entityId, amount, description, orderId, paymentId)` — delegates to `transaction.service`
- `debit(entityType, entityId, amount, description, orderId, paymentId)` — delegates to `transaction.service`
- `lockAmount(entityType, entityId, amount)` — for pending settlements
- `unlockAmount(entityType, entityId, amount)` — release lock

---

#### [NEW] [settlement.service.js](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Backend/src/core/payments/settlement.service.js)

- `createSettlement(entityType, entityId, transactionIds)` — create payout request
- `processSettlement(settlementId)` — mark as processed + unlock wallet
- `getSettlements(entityType, entityId, filters)` — list settlements

---

#### [NEW] [refund.service.js](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Backend/src/core/payments/refund.service.js)

- `initiateRefund(paymentId, amount, reason)` — create refund record + reverse transactions
- `processGatewayRefund(refundId)` — call Razorpay refund API if online payment
- `getRefundsByOrder(orderId)` — list refunds

---

### Phase 3: Order Flow Integration

---

#### [MODIFY] [order.service.js](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Backend/src/modules/food/orders/order.service.js)

Wire the new payment service into the order placement flow:
1. On order creation → call `paymentService.createPayment()` + existing `recordFoodOrderPaymentEvent()`
2. On online payment success → call `paymentService.markPaymentSuccess()` → triggers `transactionService.recordTransaction()` for user debit
3. On order delivered → trigger restaurant credit + delivery partner credit transactions
4. On order cancellation → trigger `refundService.initiateRefund()`

---

#### [MODIFY] [payment.processor.js](file:///c:/Users/SHUBHAM/Desktop/AppZeto-Master-Product-/Backend/src/queues/processors/payment.processor.js)

Currently a placeholder. Will implement:
- Process post-delivery financial splits (restaurant commission, delivery earning, platform profit)
- Create Transaction entries for each party
- Update their wallets atomically

