## Data Flow Diagram

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User Places Order] --> B{Payment Method?}
    B -->|COD| C[Create Payment status=created]
    B -->|Online| D[Create Razorpay Order]
    B -->|Wallet| E[Check Balance & Debit]
    
    D --> F[User Pays on Razorpay]
    F --> G[Webhook/Verify → markPaymentSuccess]
    
    C --> H[Payment record saved]
    E --> H
    G --> H
    
    H --> I[Record Transaction - User Debit]
    I --> J[Update User Wallet]
    
    K[Order Delivered] --> L[Payment Queue Job]
    L --> M[Record Transaction - Restaurant Credit]
    L --> N[Record Transaction - Delivery Partner Credit]
    L --> O[Record Transaction - Platform Credit]
    
    M --> P[Update Restaurant Wallet]
    N --> Q[Update Delivery Partner Wallet]
    O --> R[Update Admin Wallet]
    
    S[Order Cancelled] --> T[Initiate Refund]
    T --> U[Reverse Transactions]
    U --> V[Credit User Wallet / Gateway Refund]
```

---

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification

Since the project has no existing test framework set up, verification will be manual:

1. **Order Placement (COD)**
   - Place a COD order via the cart page
   - Verify a `Payment` document is created with `status: "created"`, `method: "cod"`
   - Verify a `Transaction` document is NOT created yet (COD settles on delivery)
   - Check MongoDB: `db.payments.find({method: "cod"}).sort({createdAt: -1}).limit(1)`

2. **Order Placement (Wallet)**
   - Ensure user has wallet balance (top up first)
   - Place a wallet order
   - Verify `Payment` created with `status: "success"`, `method: "wallet"`
   - Verify `Transaction` created with `type: "debit"` for the user
   - Verify user's `Wallet.balance` decreased by the order amount
   - Check: `db.wallets.findOne({entityId: ObjectId("<userId>"), entityType: "user"})`

3. **Order Delivery Settlement**
   - Let an order reach "delivered" status
   - Verify `Transaction` entries created for restaurant credit, delivery partner credit, and platform credit
   - Verify corresponding wallets updated
   
4. **Refund Flow**
   - Cancel an order that was paid online
   - Verify `Refund` document created
   - Verify reverse `Transaction` entries (credit back to user)
   - Verify user wallet balance restored

> [!TIP]
> **Quick Verification**: After implementing Phase 1 & 2, you can test the core services in isolation by running a simple script that calls `walletService.credit()` and checks the resulting `Transaction` and `Wallet` documents in MongoDB. I can create this script as part of implementation.

